<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>level someone • level with someone</xh5><p> <i>level someone—</i>1. knock a person down: However, Cody got cocky. He began to taunt Marshall, who <u>leveled</u> him with a football style tackle. 2. totally baffle a person; render smb. completely helpless: These questions absolutely <u>leveled</u> me. Actually, they still do; I just handle it better.</p><p><i>level with someone</i>—(coll.) give smb. one’s honest opinion; speak frankly with a person: I’d better <u>level with</u> you, son.... From now on, control is through me.</p> </entry>
